# Verify if pods are successfully deployed
kubectl get pods -n argocd

# Step 3: Setup Argo CD API & UI
### The Argo CD API server is not exposed to an external IP. To access the API server, We need to expose the argocd-server svc. I have used the AWS Load Balancer Controller for configuring ingress

## apply ingress
kubectl apply -f ingress.yaml

# This can be solved by adding the â€” insecure flag to true for the configmap. yaml
```
kubectl edit configmap argocd-cmd-params-cm -n argocd -o yaml

## Add the below given aurgment in data
data:  
  server.insecure: "true" # <-- this line need to be added

  ```

  # Restart the argocd-server
  kubectl rollout restart deployment argocd-server -n argocd

  # Now the argocd API & UI are available
  ## You can also try logging into UI (app.example.com) using the same credentials.

  # simply retrieve this password using the argocd CLI
  ```
  kubectl get secrets argocd-initial-admin-secret -o yaml -n argocd
  ```
